Boil-off rate ($\alpha$) Lognormal 0.02 day⁻¹ 0.005 day⁻¹
Transfer efficiency ($\eta$) Beta (α=95, β=5) 0.95 0.02
G-ICP accuracy ($\sigma_{GICP}$) Gamma 0.1 m 0.03 m
PSI scaling ($k$) Normal 0.35 0.05

7.5.3 Likelihood Functions

Artemis II (Lunar Flyby) provides data on:

· SLS performance (thrust variation, $I_{sp}$)
· Orion navigation accuracy
· Deep space operations

Likelihood for thrust variation given observed trajectory:

L(\sigma_T | \text{trajectory}) \propto \exp\left(-\frac{(\hat{\sigma}_T - \sigma_T)^2}{2\sigma_{\hat{\sigma}_T}^2}\right)

Artemis III (LEO Rendezvous) provides data on:

· Orbital refueling operations
· Rendezvous and docking
· Cryogenic fluid transfer
· HLS performance in LEO

Likelihood for transfer efficiency given observed transferred mass:

L(\eta | m_{transferred}) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}\sigma_m} \exp\left(-\frac{(m_{transferred} - \eta m_{tanker})^2}{2\sigma_m^2}\right)

