7.5.5 Value of Information

The expected value of perfect information (EVPI) for a parameter is:

EVPI = E_\theta[\max(0, U(a^*(\theta)) - U(a^*)]

where $a^*$ is the optimal action without perfect information, and $a^*(\theta)$ is optimal with perfect knowledge.

For thrust variation, EVPI is approximately 0.5% success probability, justifying investment in engine test instrumentation.

7.6 Loss of Crew Analysis

7.6.1 Phase-Based Decomposition

The overall probability of loss of crew (P_LOC) is decomposed into mission phases:

Table 7.6: Phase Success Probabilities (Starship Mitigated)

